	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi! I recently bought a PowerPak with a 128MB CF card. I'm using a Pal nes with the region free mod. The card works using the 128MB CF.
<br />
<br />But 128MB ain't enough so I formatted my 1GB TwinMos 140X card with Fat16. I get these errors: "Busy" and "Wrong format use Fat16/Fat32". Well I have tried to erase the partition with different kinds of utilities using Hirens bootcd and formated it with fat16 and fat32 in windows xp without success. The same errors come up. The card works fine in Mac OS X and Windows XP. Please help me!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


